=head2 Lifecycle => Str

The lifecycle status of the volume.

=over

=item *

C<AVAILABLE> - The volume is fully available for use.

=item *

C<CREATED> - The volume has been created.

=item *

C<CREATING> - Amazon FSx is creating the new volume.

=item *

C<DELETING> - Amazon FSx is deleting an existing volume.

=item *

C<FAILED> - Amazon FSx was unable to create the volume.

=item *

C<MISCONFIGURED> - The volume is in a failed but recoverable state.

=item *

C<PENDING> - Amazon FSx hasn't started creating the volume.

=back



=head2 LifecycleTransitionReason => L<Paws::FSX::LifecycleTransitionReason>

